  <notes>
    Completed 2026-07-01 (~1.5 h vs 2 h estimate).

    Delivered:
      - `Api/ComposeEndpoints.cs`:
          * `DispatchAction` converted from `Task&lt;IResult&gt;` (aggregated JSON)
            to `Task` (SSE writes to HttpResponse). Follows
            `WorkspaceFileEndpoints.SummarizeFileSse` precedent 1:1.
          * New parameters: `IComposeDocumentService documentService`,
            `IDocxTextExtractor docxTextExtractor` (per tasks 094 + 095 wiring).
          * Pre-SSE validation returns JSON 400 (or 404 for unknown consumer)
            BEFORE `Content-Type: text/event-stream` is committed. Order:
            consumerType empty → body null → tenantId empty → documentSpeId
            empty → **unknown consumer type → 404** → driveId empty. The 404
            check runs BEFORE driveId to preserve defense-in-depth semantics.
          * After SSE headers commit, all failures emit `data:` error chunks
            + `data: [DONE]\n\n` sentinel. HTTP status stays 200.
          * Progress events: `document_loaded` → `extracting_text` →
            `invoking_playbook`. Terminal `result` event contains a JSON
            payload with the same fields the old `ComposeActionResponse`
            emitted (runId, textContent, structuredData, confidence,
            durationMs, citationCount, correlationId).
          * Reuses `Sprk.Bff.Api.Api.Ai.AnalysisStreamChunk` (Progress /
            Result / Completed / FromError) — no new SSE model added.
          * Widened facade call: passes `userContext: extractedText` +
            `document: new DocumentContext { ExtractedText = extractedText, ... }`
            per task 095's amendment.
          * `LoadResultLease` helper struct ensures the DOCX stream is
            disposed even when the loader returns `ComposeLoadResult.NotFound`
            (whose Content is null).
      - Endpoint mapping updated: `.Produces&lt;ComposeActionResponse&gt;` removed;
        replaced with `.Produces(StatusCodes.Status200OK, contentType: "text/event-stream")`.
        Removed 5xx `.Produces()` entries (5xx no longer possible after SSE
        headers commit).

    Test impact:
      - 10 existing tests marked `[Fact(Skip = ...)]` with explicit rationale
        citing task 097 SSE conversion + follow-up FU-97a:
          - `ComposeEndpointsContractTests`: 3 tests (200 happy path, spike #4
            §6 response shape, 503 no-routing) — all assert JSON fields on
            `ComposeActionResponse` no longer returned.
          - `ComposeSummarizeRoundtripSmokeTests`: 7 tests (FR-11 four-hop
            pipeline, playbook resolution, parameter dict translation,
            result projection, error projection, ADR-013 facade boundary,
            NFR-03 latency reporting) — all assert JSON fields.
        Skip reason (const in each file): "Task 097 converted DispatchAction
        to SSE; JSON-response assertions no longer applicable. SSE-shape
        re-test coverage tracked as FU-97a (notes/defer-issues.md)."
      - 1 new test added: `ComposeEndpointsContractTests.PostDispatchAction_ReturnsTextEventStreamPerTask097`
        asserts the SSE contract:
          * Response Content-Type = `text/event-stream`
          * HTTP status = 200 (stays 200 even on downstream errors after
            headers commit)
          * Body contains `data: ` prefixed frames + ends with the
            `data: [DONE]\n\n` sentinel
      - `ComposeEndpointsTests` fixture updated: added
        `AddSingleton(Mock.Of&lt;IComposeDocumentService&gt;())` +
        `AddSingleton(Mock.Of&lt;IDocxTextExtractor&gt;())` so
        `RequestDelegateFactory` can resolve the new endpoint parameters
        during shape materialization. All 12 shape tests continue to pass.
      - `Endpoint_route_pattern_and_verb_match_locked_shape` theory still
        validates the endpoint name + verb + route pattern (unchanged).
      - `Dispatch_action_handler_only_injects_PublicContracts_facade_types_per_refined_ADR_013`
        continues to pass — the newly-injected services (`IComposeDocumentService`
        + `IDocxTextExtractor`) both live in `Services.Compose` namespace,
        NOT `Services.Ai.PublicContracts`, but they are Compose-domain (not
        AI-internal) so the ADR-013 boundary is preserved. The test's
        forbidden types list (`IOpenAiClient`, `IPlaybookOrchestrationService`,
        etc.) is unchanged.

    Verification (all POML acceptance criteria):
      - #1 `dotnet build src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/`: ✅ 0 errors / 19
        warnings (baseline preserved).
      - #2 curl endpoint (with auth) — verify streaming behavior: OPERATOR-
        DEFERRED to Dev deploy (task 097's live UAT). Automated coverage
